    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/1972: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-27T00:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 27, 1941—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received February 27—12:10
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>334. Embassy’s 230, February 14, 8 p.m. In the course of my conversation
                    yesterday with the Minister for Foreign Affairs I said <pb facs="0062" n="54"
                        xml:id="pg_54"/> that I wished him to know that everything Dooman had said
                    to the Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs on February 14 had my entire
                    concurrence and approval. As Mr. Matsuoka had received only an oral report of
                    the conversation from Mr. Ohashi I read to him the entire telegram under
                    reference. Somewhat to my surprise he said that he entirely agreed with what
                    Dooman had said. At the Minister’s request I am sending him today for his
                    personal use a copy of the memorandum of conversation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
